raseArch, Agogic, DurationContrast, FinalRit, Punctuation, Articulation, Microtiming) has been updated to check `applies_to(role, metadata)` before performing any mutations. The machine identity preservation requirement is satisfied by ensuring `bootstrap_identity()` is called before `FirstBootAnnouncer` in both daemon entry points (`daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAll R1–R8 rules are covered. Integration and gate tests in `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py` exhaustively verify that melodic roles are shaped while grid-locked roles (like `ostinato`) remain exactly quantized and unmutated. Identity persistence is verified by `tests/test_first_boot.py`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe shared contract follows established patterns in the render pipeline. Rule IDs (R1–R8) are consistently applied and mapped to their respective implementations. The use of `role_is_eligible` provides a single point of truth for gating logic.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNo security vulnerabilities or leaked secrets were found. Identity preservation follows the existing file-based persistence model.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe code is well-structured and follows the project's architectural standards. The integration tests provide high confidence in the behavioral correctness of the gating mechanism.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- None.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation is solid and meets all acceptance criteria. The addition of `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py` is a valuable regression anchor for the render pipeline.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260416T054258Z_1776356839.log:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260416T054258Z_1776356839.log:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v001.md:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v001.md:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v002.md:- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Startup hardening gap: `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` does not call `bootstrap_identity()` before startup announcement and main loop, while this path is still part of the runnable daemon entry points (`my-claw/docs/PROJECT_GUIDE.md` and system scripts/tests reference it), so first-boot identity creation is not guaranteed in that mode. Severity: blocking..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/templates/candidates/lead_t2/v001.md:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at firs