 leader's realized performance. The logic in `_descend_from_apex` and `_fill` accurately reflects the requirements for complementarity and filling. Specifically:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- When the leader is building (`is_building=True`), the follower's amplitude is reduced and its contour apex is inverted to complement the leader.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- When the leader is pausing (`is_pausing=True`), the follower's amplitude is boosted and its contour apex is reinforced to fill the gap.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Role metadata (`leader`, `follower`, `solo`, `tacet`) is correctly parsed and respected, with the rule only applying to voices explicitly tagged as followers.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The task is complete according to the acceptance criteria:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `CallResponseRule` implemented in `render/rules/call_response.py`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Correct transformations for building and pausing states.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Metadata role parsing covers all required keys and values.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_call_response.py` verifies both functional behavior and role-based filtering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation is consistent with other \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tier 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" render rules in `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/` (e.g., `phrase_arch.py`, `articulation.py`). It uses the shared `Event` data model and follows the `role_is_eligible` contract established in `role_gate.py`. Although `PerformanceIntent` was mentioned in the spec, it is not yet present in the codebase (targeted for T-030), and the use of the `Event` model for these transformations is the correct adaptation for the current project state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+No security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices were introduced. The implementation consists of pure-function mathematical transformations on local data structures.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The code quality is high, with clear documentation, clean dataclass abstractions, and robust role-parsing logic. The tests use Pearson correlation to verify complementarity, which is a rigorous approach for validating musical behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- None.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation successfully realizes the call-response gating requirement. The adaptation to use the `Event` model in the absence of `PerformanceIntent` is appropriate. Recurring hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` were also verified to be satisfied in the current daemon startup paths.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:05.974Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'll examine the most recent commit with `git show HEAD` to verify which files were included and confirm if\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:05.975Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" `progress.md` was inadvertently modified.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:06.016Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\