sdp/verification/t-020@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:7:- `tests/test_sampler_fx_mode_verify.py` (new)
sdp/verification/t-020@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:16:The smoke verifier (`sampler_fx_mode_verify.py`) correctly drives `EffectsBus.apply_mode(mode)` through all five canonical ArtistModes in `MODE_SEQUENCE = tuple(FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE)` order. After each call it extracts the last `/n_set` emitted for `sw_sampler_fx` and compares it against `FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE`. The assertion path in `assert_mode_snapshots_match_presets` raises loudly on any key/value drift. `capture_mode_snapshots` also validates `current_mode` state after each apply, covering both the bus state and the emitted OSC message.
sdp/verification/t-020@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:22:All five ArtistModes are exercised: `solitary`, `companion`, `working_ambience`, `evening_reflection`, `storm`. The smoke entry point is hardware-free, as required by the task spec. Documentation was updated in both `cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` and `cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to register `sampler_fx_mode_verify.py` in the landed-components table and inline the `EffectsBus.apply_mode` call site into the dispatch-flow description. The architecture test's `LANDED_COMPONENTS` tuple was extended to include the new verifier path.
sdp/verification/t-020@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:24:One gap noted (non-blocking): `test_sampler_fx_mode_verify.py` uses a raw `sys.path.insert` to import `sampler_fx_mode_verify` since the file lives in `my-claw/tools/` outside the installed package. This is consistent with how `sample_capture_verify.py` is handled and does not affect correctness.
sdp/verification/t-020@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:28:The smoke verifier follows the exact pattern of `sample_capture_verify.py` (hardware-free, deterministic, no live audio required). Test naming mirrors the `test_sampler_dispatch.py` style. `MODE_SEQUENCE` is derived from `tuple(FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE)` rather than hardcoded, so it stays in sync automatically if the preset table grows. The OSC recording stub (`_RecordingOSC`) in the verifier matches the in-test stub pattern.
sdp/verification/t-020@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:36:3420 tests pass (`pytest tests/ -x -q`). The 39 targeted sampler tests all pass in 0.13 s. The three new `test_sampler_fx_mode_verify` tests cover: correct per-mode snapshot order and values, drift rejection, and the `main()` success-marker output. Code is minimal and self-contained.
sdp/verification/t-020@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:42:- [ ] `sys.path.insert` import in `test_sampler_fx_mode_verify.py` — severity: minor. Non-blocking; matches the pre-existing pattern for tools outside the installed package namespace.
